==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Io moth
<hw>I"o moth`</hw> <pr>(?; 115)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large
and handsome American moth (<spn>Hyperchiria Io</spn>), having a large,
bright-colored spot on each hind wing, resembling the spots on the tail
of a peacock. The larva is covered with prickly hairs, which sting like
nettles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>-ion</ent>⟦br⟧
